===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs {{och-l|髓|tr= {{IPAfont|*soiʔ}}}} further from uncertainly reconstructed ancestor {{IPAfont|*swaiʔ}}, which he deems possibly related to {{cog|sit-pro|*swiʔ||blood}}, some of whose reflexes mean "marrow": e.g. {{cog|kac|lə səwi|lə '''səwi'''}}, {{cog|mhu|tr= ɹu⁵³ '''su⁵³'''}}, {{cog|duu|tr= mɯ³¹ '''sĭʔ⁵⁵'''}}, {{cog|lif|tr= siː}}, {{cog|nbc|tr= hʌ̀i}}.

However, the Old Chinese pronunciation of {{zh-l|*髓}} is also reconstructed as {{IPAfont|*slolʔ}} ({{w|Reconstructions of Old Chinese#Zhengzhang (1981–1995)|ZS}}) and {{IPAfont|*s-lojʔ}} ({{w|Reconstructions of Old Chinese#Baxter–Sagart (2014)|B-S}}) with medial *{{IPAfont|-l-}}, if so, it would be unrelated to {{m|sit-pro|*swiʔ}}.

